parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door sensors can cause the doors not to lock, interior and puddle lights to remain on, drain the battery, and doors won't lock even when the car is in motion. This can lead to safety issues, such as the doors opening while driving, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The door sensor says the car door is open even when it is firmly shut
doors not locking
interior and puddle lights remaining on
battery draining
and doors not locking even when the car is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Touch Screen and Infotainment System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty touch screen and infotainment system can cause inconvenience to the driver and passengers, and potentially lead to safety issues if the rear camera and blind spot warning systems are not functioning properly.
symptoms: The touch screen goes black
the screen does not turn on
the rear camera does not work
and the blind spot warning and rear cross traffic warning systems do not function.

brake pads

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty collision sensor and electrical/electronics can cause inconvenience to the driver and passengers, and potentially lead to safety issues if the systems are not functioning properly.
